EEE\n| colspan=\"3\" | [[List of Presidents of the National Assembly of France|President of the National Assembly]]<br/>{{small|(3 December 1946 {{ndash}} 20 January 1947)}}\n|- \n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"background:{{National Centre of Independents and Peasants/meta/color}}; color:white;\" | 17\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[Image:Ren\u00e9 Coty portrait officiel.jpg|100px]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" | '''[[Ren\u00e9 Coty]]'''<br/>{{small|[[Legion of Honour|GCLH]]}}<br/>(1882{{ndash}}1962)\n| 16 January 1954\n| 8 January 1959\n| [[List of indirect presidential elections in France|{{smaller|1953}}]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[National Centre of Independents and Peasants|CNIP]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" | <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elysee.fr/president/la-presidence/le-president-de-la-republique/histoire-des-presidents-de-la-republique/rene-coty-1882-1962.5367.html |title=Ren\u00e9 Coty (1882\u20131962) |publisher=Official website of the French Presidency |language=French |accessdate=2 August 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100413113645/http://www.elysee.fr/president/la-presidence/le-president-de-la-republique/histoire-des-presidents-de-la-republique/rene-coty-1882-1962.5367.html |archivedate=13 April 2010 }}</ref>\n|-\n|- bgcolor=#EEEEEE\n| colspan=\"3\" | [[Council of the Republic (France)|Vice President of the Council of the Republic]]<br/>{{small|(19 November 1948 {{ndash}} 14 January 1954)}}\n|-\n| colspan=\"8\" |\n\n===[[French Fifth Republic]] (1958{{ndash}}present)===\n|-\n! rowspan=\"3\" style=\"background:{{Union of Democrats for the Republic/meta/color}}; color:white;\" | 18\n| rowspan=\"3\" | [[Image:Bundesarchiv B 145 Bild-F010324-0002, Flughafen K\u00f6ln-Bonn, Adenauer, de Gaulle-cropped.jpg|100px]]\n| rowspan=\"3\" align=\"center\" | '''[[Charles de Gaulle]]'''<br/>{{small|[[Legion of Honour|GCLH]] [[National Order of Merit (France)|GCM]] [[Order of Liberation|CL]] [[Croix de guerre 1914\u20131918 (France)|Cg (1914)]] [[Croix de guerre 1939\u20131945 (France)|Cg (1939)]] [[Combatant's Cross|CC]] [[1914\u20131918 Inter-Allied Victory medal (France)|MIV]] [[1914\u20131918 Commemorative war medal (France)|Mcg]]}}<br/>(1890{{ndash}}1970)\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 8 January 1959\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 28 April 1969\n| [[List of indirect presidential elections in France|{{smaller|1958}}]]\n| [[Union for the New Republic|UNR]]<br/>{{small|(1959{{ndash}}1967)}}\n| rowspan=\"3\" | <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elysee.fr/president/la-presidence/le-president-de-la-republique/histoire-des-presidents-de-la-republique/charles-de-gaulle-1890-1970.5356.html |title=Charles de Gaulle (1890\u20131970) |publisher=Official website of the French Presidency |language=French |accessdate=2 August 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100401073841/http://www.elysee.fr/president/la-presidence/le-president-de-la-republique/histoire-des-presidents-de-la-republique/charles-de-gaulle-1890-1970.5356.html |archivedate=1 April 2010 }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[1965 French presidential election|{{smaller|1965}}]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[Union of Democrats for the Republic|UDR]]<br/>{{small|(1967{{ndash}}1969)}}\n|-\n|- bgcolor=#EEEEEE\n| colspan=\"3\" | [[Prime Minister of France|President of the Council of Ministers]]<br/>{{small|(1 June 1958 {{ndash}} 8 January 1959)}}\n|-\n|- bgcolor=#FFFFE0\n| colspan=7\" | The President of the Senate ''[[Alain Poher]]'' deputised during the interim (28 April 1969 {{ndash}} 20 June 1969).\n| <ref name=\"Poher\">{{cite web|url=http://www.elysee.fr/president/la-presidence/le-president-de-la-republique/histoire-des-presidents-de-la-republique/alain-poher-1909-1996.5329.html |title=Alain Poher (1909\u20131996) |publisher=Official website of the French Presidency |language=French |accessdate=2 August 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100413113625/http://www.elysee.fr/president/la-presidence/le-president-de-la-republique/histoire-des-presidents-de-la-republique/alain