3635/http://www.elysee.fr/president/la-presidence/le-president-de-la-republique/histoire-des-presidents-de-la-republique/albert-lebrun-1871-1950.5370.html |archivedate=13 April 2010 }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[List of indirect presidential elections in France|{{smaller|1939}}]]\n|-\n|- bgcolor=#EEEEEE\n| colspan=\"3\" | [[List of Presidents of the Senate of France|President of the Senate]]<br/>{{small|(11 June 1931 {{ndash}} 10 May 1932)}}\n|-\n|- bgcolor=#EEEEEE\n| colspan=\"8\" | After the fall of Third Republic and the establishment of the collaborationist [[Vichy France|French State]] led by Marshal [[Philippe P\u00e9tain]], the presidency became vacant from 11 July 1940 to 20 August 1944.\n|-\n| colspan=\"8\" | \n===[[French Fourth Republic]] (1944{{ndash}}1958)===\n|-\n|- bgcolor=#FFFFE0\n| colspan=\"8\" | The Chairmen of the ''[[Provisional Government of the French Republic|Provisional Government]]'' deputised during the interim (20 August 1944 {{ndash}} 16 January 1947).\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"background:{{French Section of the Workers' International/meta/color}}; color:white;\" | 16\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[Image:Portrait officiel Vincent Auriol.jpg|100px]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" | '''[[Vincent Auriol]]'''<br/>{{small|[[Legion of Honour|GCLH]] [[Resistance Medal|MR]]}}<br/>(1884{{ndash}}1966)\n| 16 January 1947\n| 16 January 1954\n| [[List of indirect presidential elections in France|{{smaller|1947}}]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[French Section of the Workers' International|SFIO]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" | <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elysee.fr/president/la-presidence/le-president-de-la-republique/histoire-des-presidents-de-la-republique/vincent-auriol-1884-1966.5369.html |title=Vincent Auriol (1884\u20131966) |publisher=Official website of the French Presidency |language=French |accessdate=2 August 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100413113651/http://www.elysee.fr/president/la-presidence/le-president-de-la-republique/histoire-des-pres