31996) |publisher=Official website of the French Presidency |language=French |accessdate=2 August 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100401073846/http://www.elysee.fr/president/la-presidence/le-president-de-la-republique/histoire-des-presidents-de-la-republique/francois-mitterrand-1916-1996.5312.html |archivedate=1 April 2010 }}</ref>\n|- \n| [[1988 French presidential election|{{smaller|1988}}]]\n|-\n|- bgcolor=#EEEEEE\n| colspan=\"3\" | Member of the [[National Assembly (France)|National Assembly]] for [[Ni\u00e8vre]]<br/>{{small|(6 December 1962 {{ndash}} 21 May 1981)}}\n|-\n! rowspan=\"3\" style=\"background:{{Union for a Popular Movement/meta/color}}; color:white;\" | 22\n| rowspan=\"3\" | [[Image:Jacques Chirac (1997) (cropped).jpg|100px]]\n| rowspan=\"3\" align=\"center\" | '''[[Jacques Chirac]]'''<br/>{{small|[[Legion of Honour|GCLH]] [[National Order of Merit (France)|GCM]] [[Cross for Military Valour|CVM]] [[Order of Agricultural Merit|COMA]] [[Ordre des Arts et des Lettres|COAL]] [[Aeronautical Medal|MA]] [[North Africa Security and Order Operations Commemorative Medal|''Alg\u00e9rie'']] [[Order of the Black Star|COEN]]}}<br/>(1932{{ndash}}2019)\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 17 May 1995\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 16 May 2007\n| [[1995 French presidential election|{{smaller|1995}}]]\n| [[Rally for the Republic|RPR]]<br/>{{small|(1995{{ndash}}2002)}}\n| rowspan=\"3\" | <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elysee.fr/president/la-presidence/le-president-de-la-republique/histoire-des-presidents-de-la-republique/jacques-chirac-1932.5308.html |title=Jacques Chirac (1932) |publisher=Official website of the French Presidency |language=French |accessdate=2 August 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100628160122/http://www.elysee.fr/president/la-presidence/le-president-de-la-republique/histoire-des-presidents-de-la-republique/jacques-chirac-1932.5308.html |archivedate=28 June 2010 }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[2002 French presidential election|{{smaller|2002}}]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[Union for a Popular Movement|UMP]]<br/>{{small|(2002{{ndash}}2007)}}\n|-\n|- bgcolor=#EEEEEE\n| colspan=\"3\" | [[List of mayors of Paris|Mayor of Paris]]<br/>{{small|(25 March 1977 {{ndash}} 16 May 1995)}}\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"background:{{Union for a Popular Movement/meta/color}}; color:white;\" | 23\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[Image:Flickr - europeanpeoplesparty - EPP Summit October 2010 (105).jpg|100px]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" | '''[[Nicolas Sarkozy]]'''<br/>{{small|[[Legion of Honour|GCLH]] [[National Order of Merit (France)|GCM]]}}<br/>(born 1955)\n| 16 May 2007\n| 15 May 2012\n| [[2007 French presidential election|{{smaller|2007}}]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[Union for a Popular Movement|UMP]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" | <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elysee.fr/president/la-presidence/les-presidents-depuis-1848/histoire-des-presidents-de-la-republique/nicolas-sarkozy-2007-2012.13207.html |title=Nicolas Sarkozy (1955) |publisher=Official website of the French Presidency |language=French |accessdate=15 May 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120518080748/http://www.elysee.fr/president/la-presidence/les-presidents-depuis-1848/histoire-des-presidents-de-la-republique/nicolas-sarkozy-2007-2012.13207.html |archivedate=18 May 2012 }}</ref>\n|-\n|- bgcolor=#EEEEEE\n| colspan=\"3\" | [[List of Interior Ministers of France|Minister of the Interior]]<br/>{{small|(2 June 2005 {{ndash}} 26 March 2007)}}\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"background:{{Socialist Party (France)/meta/color}}; color:white;\" | 24\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[Image:Francois Hollande 2015.jpeg|100px]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" | '''[[Fran\u00e7ois Hollande]]'''<br/>{{small|[[Legion of Honour|GCLH]] [[National Order of Merit (France)|GCM]]}}<br/>(born 1954)\n| 15 May 2012\n| 14 May 2017\n| [[2012 French presidential election|{{smaller|2012}}]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[Socialist Party (France)|PS]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" | <ref name=\"elysee-francis-hollande-482\">{{cite web|url=http://www.elysee.fr/president/la-presidence/le-president-de-la-republique/francois-hollande-biographie/francois-hollande.482.html |title=Biographie officielle de Fran\u00e7ois Hollande |publisher=Official website of the French Presidency |language=French |trans-title=Official biography of Fran\u00e7ois Hollande |accessdate=15 May 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120518070336/http://www.elysee.fr/president/la-presidence/le-president-de-la-republique/francois-hollande-biographie/francois-hollande.482.html |archivedate=18 May 2012 }}</ref>\n|-\n|- bgcolor=#EEEEEE\n| colspan=\"3\" | [[List of Presidents of Corr\u00e8ze General Council|President of the General Council of Corr\u00e8ze]]<br/>{{small|(20 March 2008 {{ndash}} 11 May 2012)}}\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"background:{{La R\u00e9publique En Marche!/meta/color}}; color:black;\" | 25\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[Image:Emmanuel Macron in 2019.jpg|100px]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" | '''[[Emmanuel Macron]]'''<br/>{{small|[[Legion of Honour|GCLH]] [[National Order of Merit (France)|GCM]]}}<br/>(born 1977)\n| 14 May 2017\n| Incumbent\n| [[2017 French presidential election|{{smaller|2017}}]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[La R\u00e9publique En Marche!|LREM]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" | <ref name=\"elysee-francis-hollande-482\" />\n|-\n|- bgcolor=#EEEEEE\n| colspan=\"3\" | [[List of Finance Ministers of France|Minister of the Economy, Industry and Digital Affairs]]<br/>{{small|(26 August 2014 {{ndash}} 30 August 2016)}}\n|}\n\n==Graphical timeline (Fifth Republic)==\n{{#tag:timeline|\nImageSize = width:875 height:auto barincrement:12\nPlotArea  = top:10 bottom:50 right:130 left:20\nAlignBars = late\n\nDefine $today = {{#time:d/m/Y}}\n\nDateFormat=dd/mm/yyyy\nPeriod     = from:01/01/1959 till:$today\nTimeAxis   = orientation:horizontal\nScaleMajor = unit:year increment:5 start:1960\nScaleMinor = unit:year increment:1 start:1959\n\nColors     =\n  id:socialist value:rgb(1,0.2,0.4)\