{"title_page": "Kasetsart University", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2017}}\n{{Infobox university\n| name = Kasetsart University\n| native_name = {{lang|th|\u0e21\u0e2b\u0e32\u0e27\u0e34\u0e17\u0e22\u0e32\u0e25\u0e31\u0e22\u0e40\u0e01\u0e29\u0e15\u0e23\u0e28\u0e32\u0e2a\u0e15\u0e23\u0e4c}}\n| image_name = [[File:Kasetsart_University_logo_eng.jpeg|180px]]\n| image_size = \n| image_alt = \n| caption = [[Varuna|Phra Phirun mounted on a naga]]\n| latin_name = \n| motto = * \u0e28\u0e32\u0e2a\u0e15\u0e23\u0e4c\u0e41\u0e2b\u0e48\u0e07\u0e41\u0e1c\u0e48\u0e19\u0e14\u0e34\u0e19 ''(official)''\n* \u0e1b\u0e23\u0e30\u0e0a\u0e32\u0e0a\u0e19 \u0e04\u0e37\u0e2d \u0e40\u0e08\u0e49\u0e32\u0e02\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e1b\u0e23\u0e30\u0e40\u0e17\u0e28 \u0e40\u0e01\u0e29\u0e15\u0e23\u0e28\u0e32\u0e2a\u0e15\u0e23\u0e4c \u0e04\u0e37\u0e2d \u0e20\u0e32\u0e29\u0e35\u0e02\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e1b\u0e23\u0e30\u0e0a\u0e32\u0e0a\u0e19 ''(unofficial)''\n| mottoeng = * Knowledge of the Land ''(official)''\n* People own the nation and their taxes become Kasetsart ''(unofficial)''\n| established = {{Start date|1943|02|02}}\n| founders = Luang Suwan Vajokkasikij <br> Phra Chuangkasetsinlapakan <br> Luang Ingkhasikasikan\n| closed = \n| type = [[National university|National]]\n| affiliation = \n| endowment = \n| budget = \n| officer_in_charge = \n| chairman = \n| chancellor = \n| president = Chongrak Wachrinrat, Ph.D. ''(acting)''<ref>{{cite web|title=The University Administration|url=http://www.ku.ac.th/web2012/index.php?c=adms&m=linkmenu_eng&time=20130815101758&load=&lang=eng&ip=1&id=175&page=About%20KU&page1=|website=Kasetsart University|accessdate=16 October 2015}}</ref>\n| vice-president = \n| superintendent = \n| provost = \n| vice_chancellor = \n| rector = \n| principal = \n| dean = \n| director = \n| head_label = \n| head = \n| academic_staff = 3,805 (2017)<ref name=KU-Admin>{{cite web|title=Administration: Number of Personnel|url=http://www.person.ku.ac.th/new_personweb/stat/2560/rpt_person_May60.xlsx|website=Kasetsart University|accessdate=19 October 2017}}</ref>\n| administrative_staff = \n| students = 86,536 (2019)<ref name=KU-TotStudents>{{cite web|title=Total Students|url=https://www.regis.ku.ac.th/cpcmns/rpt_std_ku3.php|website=Kasetsart University|accessdate=23 July 2019}}</ref>\n| undergrad = 76,245 (2019)\n| postgrad = 8,816 (2019)\n| doctoral = 1,475 (2019)\n| other = \n| city = [[Chatuchak District|Chatuchak]]\n| state = [[Bangkok]]\n| country = [[Thailand]]\n| coor = {{coord|13|50|54.95|N|100|34|04.98|E|type:edu|display=title,inline}}\n| campus = [[Urban area|Urban]] and [[Rural]] (varied by campus)\n| former_names = College of Agriculture\n| free_label = Anthem\n| free = \"Kasetsart\"\n| colours = {{color box|#006664}} [[Green|Forest Green]]<ref name=symbols>{{cite web|title=Kasetsart Symbol|url=http://www.ku.ac.th/web2012/index.php?c=adms&m=linkmenu_eng&time=20120627124210&load=&lang=eng&ip=1&id=18&page=About%20KU&page1=|website=Kasetsart University|accessdate=29 August 2015}}</ref>\n| athletics = \n| sports = \n| nickname = \n| mascot = [[Peltophorum pterocarpum|Nontri (tree)]]<ref name=symbols />\n| affiliations = [[Association of Southeast Asian Institutions of Higher Learning|ASAIHL]]\n| website = {{url|http://ku.ac.th}}\n| logo = \n| footnotes = \n}}\n'''Kasetsart University''' ({{lang-th|\u0e21\u0e2b\u0e32\u0e27\u0e34\u0e17\u0e22\u0e32\u0e25\u0e31\u0e22\u0e40\u0e01\u0e29\u0e15\u0e23\u0e28\u0e32\u0e2a\u0e15\u0e23\u0e4c}}; {{RTGS|Mahawitthayalai Kasetsat}}) (KU) is a [[public university|public research university]] in Bangkok, [[Thailand]]. It was Thailand's first [[agriculture|agricultural]] university and Thailand's third oldest university.{{Citation needed|date=March 2018}} It was established on 2 February 1943 to promote subjects related to [[agricultural science]]. Since then, Kasetsart University has expanded its subject areas to cover [[life sciences]], [[science]], [[engineering]], [[social sciences]], and [[humanities]]. Kasetsart University's main campus is in Bangkhen, northern Bangkok, with several other campuses throughout Thailand. It is the largest university in Thailand.{{Citation needed|date=March 2018}}\n\n== History ==\n\n[[File:Benbadhanabongse.jpg|150px|thumb|left|Prince Benbadhnabongse, the Prince of Phichai]]\n\nIn 1902, [[King Chulalongkorn]] attempted to promote the country's silk, silverware, and weaving industries. He hired Dr Kametaro Toyama, from the [[University of Tokyo]], to train Siamese students in Japanese silk and weaving crafts.<ref>Japan International Research Center for Agricultural Sciences [http://www.jircas.affrc.go.jp/english/publication/jarq/03-4/03-4-030-033.pdf \"A Scientist and a Link of the Chain uniting Thailand and Japan\"] Retrieved 2017-01-02</ref> In 1904, the School of Sericulture was founded at [[Pathum Wan District|Tambon Thung Saladaeng]], [[Bangkok]] by [[Benbadhanabongse|Prince Benbadhanabongse]], the Director of the Department of Sericulture of the Ministry of Agriculture.<ref>\u0e01\u0e23\u0e21\u0e2b\u0e21\u0e48\u0e2d\u0e19\u0e44\u0e2b\u0e21 [http://qsds.go.th/newqsds/inside_page.php?pageid=10 \u0e1b\u0e23\u0e30\u0e27\u0e31\u0e15\u0e34\u0e01\u0e23\u0e21\u0e2b\u0e21\u0e48\u0e2d\u0e19\u0e44\u0e2b\u0e21] Retrieved 2017-01-02</ref> The school was renamed the School of Agriculture in 1906.\n\nIn 1908, the School of the Ministry of Agriculture was founded at [[Windsor Palace (Thailand)|Windsor Palace]] as the [[Ministry of Agriculture and Cooperatives (Thailand)|Ministry of Agriculture]] merged three schools, the School of Surveying (founded in 1882), the School of Irrigation (founded in 1905), and the School of Agriculture. Thailand's first tertiary-level agriculture curriculum began to offer courses in 1909.\n\nIn 1917, Phraya Thepsartsatit and [[Chaophraya Thammasakmontri]] of the Ministry of Education founded the first primary school of agriculture under the Ministry of Agriculture, named the Primary School Agriculture Teacher Training School in [[Pathum Wan District|Tambon Horwang]]. It moved to [[Mueang Nakhon Pathom District|Tambon Phra Prathon]], [[Nakhon Pathom Province]] in 1918.<ref>\u0e21\u0e2b\u0e32\u0e27\u0e34\u0e17\u0e22\u0e32\u0e25\u0e31\u0e22\u0e40\u0e01\u0e29\u0e15\u0e23\u0e28\u0e32\u0e2a\u0e15\u0e23\u0e4c [http://pirun.ku.ac.th/~fedupst/Chapter4.pdf \u0e01\u0e32\u0e23\u0e1e\u0e31\u0e12\u0e19\u0e32\u0e2d\u0e32\u0e0a\u0e35\u0e27\u0e40\u0e01\u0e29\u0e15\u0e23\u0e01\u0e23\u0e23\u0e21] Retrieved 2017-01-02</ref>\n\nIn 1931, [[Sithiporn Kridakara|Prince Sithiporn Kridakara]] and Chaophraya Thammasakmontri together expanded the school regionally. In the central region, a campus was located in [[Saraburi Province]], in the northern region in [[Chiang Mai Province]], in the northeastern region in [[Nakhon Ratchasima Province]], and in the southern region in [[Songkhla Province]].\n\n[[File:Monuments_of_the_3_Masters_of_Kasetsart_University.jpg|250px|thumb|right|Statue of the Three Masters of Kasetsart University]]\n\nIn 1935, the Primary School Agriculture Teacher Training School in each part of the country was closed and merged following the agricultural education policy in that time. Luang Ingkhasikasikan, Luang Suwan Vajokkasikij, and Phra Chuangkasetsinlapakan<ref>[http://www.ku.ac.th/about/history_ku.html \u0e1a\u0e38\u0e04\u0e04\u0e25\u0e2a\u0e33\u0e04\u0e31\u0e0d\u0e02\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e21\u0e2b\u0e32\u0e27\u0e34\u0e17\u0e22\u0e32\u0e25\u0e31\u0e22] \u0e40\u0e23\u0e35\u0e22\u0e01\u0e14\u0e39\u0e27\u0e31\u0e19\u0e17\u0e35\u0e48 2013-02-21</ref> together proposed to maintain the Mae Jo School (today's [[Mae Jo University]]) at Chiang Mai Province only and renamed it Secondary-level Agriculture Technical School before it was elevated to the College of Agriculture, under the Department of Agriculture and Fisheries.\n\nThe Ministry of Agriculture established the Central Agriculture Station or \"Kaset Klang\", in [[Bang Khen District]], Bangkok. It caused the College of Agriculture to move to Bang Khen District in 1938 and the government office at Chiang Mai Province became [[Mae Jo University|Kasetsart Preparatory School]] to prepare students to study at the College of Agriculture in Bang Khen.\n[[File:\u0e41\u0e1b\u0e25\u0e01 \u0e1e\u0e34\u0e1a\u0e39\u0e25\u0e2a\u0e07\u0e04\u0e23\u0e32\u0e21 \u0e23\u0e39\u0e1b\u0e2d\u0e22\u0e48\u0e32\u0e07\u0e40\u0e1b\u0e47\u0e19\u0e17\u0e32\u0e07\u0e01\u0e32\u0e23.jpg|thumb|left|Prime Minister Plaek Phibunsongkhram|120px]]\nIn 1943, [[Plaek Phibunsongkhram|Field Marshal Plaek Phibunsongkhram]] promoted the College of Agriculture and established Kasetsart University as a department of the Ministry of Agriculture.<ref>\u0e23\u0e32\u0e0a\u0e01\u0e34\u0e08\u0e08\u0e32\u0e19\u0e38\u0e40\u0e1a\u0e01\u0e29\u0e32 [http://www.ratchakitcha.soc.go.th/DATA/PDF/2486/A/007/228.PDF \u0e1e\u0e23\u0e30\u0e23\u0e32\u0e0a\u0e1a\u0e31\u0e0d\u0e0d\u0e31\u0e15\u0e34\u0e21\u0e2b\u0e32\u0e27\u0e34\u0e17\u0e22\u0e32\u0e25\u0e31\u0e22\u0e40\u0e01\u0e29\u0e15\u0e23\u0e28\u0e32\u0e2a\u0e15\u0e23\u0e4c \u0e1e\u0e38\u0e17\u0e18\u0e28\u0e31\u0e01\u0e23\u0e32\u0e0a \u0e52\u0e54\u0e58\u0e56] Retrieved 2017-01-02</ref> The university consisted of four faculties: agriculture, fisheries, forestry, and cooperatives (today's Faculty of Economics and Faculty of Business Administration).<ref>\u0e23\u0e32\u0e0a\u0e01\u0e34\u0e08\u0e08\u0e32\u0e19\u0e38\u0e40\u0e1a\u0e01\u0e29\u0e32 [http://www.ratchakitcha.soc.go.th/DATA/PDF/2486/A/007/228.PDF \u0e1e\u0e23\u0e30\u0e23\u0e32\u0e0a\u0e1a\u0e31\u0e0d\u0e0d\u0e31\u0e15\u0e34\u0e21\u0e2b\u0e32\u0e27\u0e34\u0e17\u0e22\u0e32\u0e25\u0e31\u0e22\u0e40\u0e01\u0e29\u0e15\u0e23\u0e28\u0e32\u0e2a\u0e15\u0e23\u0e4c \u0e1e.\u0e28. \u0e52\u0e54\u0e58\u0e56] Retrieved 2017-01-02</ref>\n\nIn 1966, [[Chuchat Kamphu|Mom Luang Xujati Kambhu]], the Fifth President of Kasetsart University, judged the Bang Khen campus too confined and unable to support the education in agricultural sciences called for by the National Social and Economics Development Plan.<ref>[http://archives.psd.ku.ac.th/kuout/p013.html \u0e1b\u0e23\u0e30\u0e27\u0e31\u0e15\u0e34\u0e21\u0e2b\u0e32\u0e27\u0e34\u0e17\u0e22\u0e32\u0e25\u0e31\u0e22] Retrieved 2017-01-02</ref> The [[Kamphaeng Saen District|Kamphaeng Saen campus]] was established on 12 November 1979 as a result.<ref>[http://www.ku.ac.th/newdesign/content_level.php?menulevel=22 \u0e1b\u0e23\u0e30\u0e27\u0e31\u0e15\u0e34\u0e21\u0e2b\u0e32\u0e27\u0e34\u0e17\u0e22\u0e32\u0e25\u0e31\u0e22\u0e17\u0e28\u0e27\u0e23\u0e23\u0e29\u0e17\u0e35\u0e48\u0e2a\u0e35\u0e48 \u0e1e.\u0e28. 2516-2525] Retrieved 2017-01-02</ref>\n\nThe university further expanded by establishing [[Si Racha District|Sriracha campus]], [[Sakon Nakhon Province|Chalermphrakiat Sakon Nakhon Province campus]], [[Suphan Buri Province|Suphan Buri campus]], [[Krabi Province|Krabi campus]] and [[Lopburi Province|Lopburi campus]]. The university already established Si Racha campus in 1989<ref>[http://www.src.ku.ac.th/WebEng/index2.php?iPage=info/abCampus.html History of the Campus] Retrieved 2017-01-02</ref> and the Chalermphrakiat Sakon Nakhon Province campus on 15 August 1996.<ref>[http://www.csc.ku.ac.th/index.php/en/about-us/about-university/about-the-kucsc About KU.CSC] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170103165335/http://www.csc.ku.ac.th/index.php/en/about-us/about-university/about-the-kucsc |date=3 January 2017 }} Retrieved 2017-01-02</ref>\n\nOn 18 July 2015, the Kasetsart University Act B.E. 2558 (2015) transformed it from a [[public university]] to a [[national university]].<ref>[http://www.ratchakitcha.soc.go.th/DATA/PDF/2558/A/066/1.PDF \u0e1e\u0e23\u0e30\u0e23\u0e32\u0e0a\u0e1a\u0e31\u0e0d\u0e0d\u0e31\u0e15\u0e34\u0e21\u0e2b\u0e32\u0e27\u0e34\u0e17\u0e22\u0e32\u0e25\u0e31\u0e22\u0e40\u0e01\u0e29\u0e15\u0e23\u0e28\u0e32\u0e2a\u0e15\u0e23\u0e4c \u0e1e.\u0e28. \u0e52\u0e55\u0e55\u0e58] Retrieved 2017-01-02</ref>\n\n==Symbols==\n===Phra Phirun===\nKasetsart University's symbol is [[Varuna|Phra Phirun]], the god of rain mounted on a [[N\u0101ga]] with encircled by [[Nelumbo|lotus petals]] and then by the words \"\u0e21\u0e2b\u0e32\u0e27\u0e34\u0e17\u0e22\u0e32\u0e25\u0e31\u0e22\u0e40\u0e01\u0e29\u0e15\u0e23\u0e28\u0e32\u0e2a\u0e15\u0e23\u0e4c \u0e1e.\u0e28. \u0e52\u0e54\u0e58\u0e56\" in the Thai version and \"KASETSART UNIVERSITY 1943\" in the English version.<ref name=logo>\u0e23\u0e32\u0e0a\u0e01\u0e34\u0e08\u0e08\u0e32\u0e19\u0e38\u0e40\u0e1a\u0e01\u0e29\u0e32 [http://www.ratchakitcha.soc.go.th/DATA/PDF/2552/E/098/34.PDF \u0e01\u0e33\u0e2b\u0e19\u0e14\u0e20\u0e32\u0e1e\u0e40\u0e04\u0e23\u0e37\u0e48\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e2b\u0e21\u0e32\u0e22\u0e23\u0e32\u0e0a\u0e01\u0e32\u0e23 \u0e15\u0e32\u0e21\u0e1e\u0e23\u0e1a.\u0e40\u0e04\u0e23\u0e37\u0e48\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e2b\u0e21\u0e32\u0e22\u0e23\u0e32\u0e0a\u0e01\u0e32\u0e23 \u0e1e.\u0e28. 2482 \u0e25\u0e07\u0e27\u0e31\u0e19\u0e17\u0e35\u0e48 \u0e51\u0e53 \u0e01\u0e23\u0e01\u0e0e\u0e32\u0e04\u0e21 \u0e52\u0e55\u0e55\u0e52] Retrieved 2017-01-02</ref>\n\n[[File:Main Auditorium of Kasetsart University.jpg|thumb|300px|Nine nontri trees in front of KU's main auditorium]]\n\n===Nontri tree===\nThe [[Peltophorum pterocarpum|nontri tree]] has been a symbol of Kasetsart University since 1963. The [[Bhumibol Adulyadej|king]] and [[Sirikit|queen]] planted nine nontri trees in the front of Kasetsart University's main auditorium on 29 November 1963 which became historic day for Nisit Kasetsart.<ref>[http://www.ku.ac.th/aboutku/thai/nontri.htm \u0e21\u0e2b\u0e32\u0e27\u0e34\u0e17\u0e22\u0e32\u0e25\u0e31\u0e22\u0e40\u0e01\u0e29\u0e15\u0e23\u0e28\u0e32\u0e2a\u0e15\u0e23\u0e4c: \u0e15\u0e49\u0e19\u0e19\u0e19\u0e17\u0e23\u0e35] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101201082549/http://www.ku.ac.th/aboutku/thai/nontri.htm |date=1 December 2010 }} Retrieved 2017-01-02</ref>\n\nThe nontri is a tree in the [[Fabaceae|family Fabaceae]]. It is a long-lived evergreen with grey-brown bark with upright branches. The leaves are [[bipinnate]] compound and the flowers are yellow, produced in large compound [[racemes]]. Its fruit is a pod containing seeds.\n\n== Organization ==\n[[Image:Kasetsart University Thailand Bldg.jpg|thumb|200px|right|Kasetsart Golden Jubilee Administrative and Information Center at Bang Khen Campus]]\n\n===Bangkhen===\nKasetsart University occupies 846 [[Rai (unit)|rai]] (135 hectares) in [[Chatuchak District]], [[Bangkok]].\n{{colbegin}}\n* Faculty of Agriculture\n* Faculty of Agro-Industry\n* Faculty of Architecture\n* Faculty of Business Administration\n* Faculty of Economics\n* Faculty of Education\n* Faculty of Engineering\n* Faculty of Environment\n* Faculty of Fisheries\n* Faculty of Forestry\n* Faculty of Humanities\n* Faculty of Science\n* Faculty of Social Sciences\n* Faculty of Veterinary Medicine\n* Faculty of Veterinary Technology\n* Graduate School\n* College of Integrated Science\n{{colend}}\n[[Image:Picture of faculty sportscience kasetsart university.jpg|thumb|200px|right|Faculty of Sport Science at Kamphaeng Saen campus]]\n\n===Kamphaeng Saen Campus===\nThe Kamphaeng Saen Campus is the first and largest branch of Kasetsart University established in 1979. The campus is situated in [[Kamphaeng Saen District]], [[Nakhon Pathom Province]] with the area of 7,951.75 rai (1272 hectares).\n{{colbegin}}\n* Faculty of Agriculture at Kamphaeng Saen\n* Faculty of Engineering at Kamphaeng Saen\n* Faculty of Education and Development Sciences\n* Faculty of Liberal Arts and Science\n* Faculty of Sports Science\n* Faculty of Veterinary Medicine at Kamphaeng Saen\n{{colend}}\n\n===Sriracha Campus===\nThe Sriracha Campus was established in 1988, and occupies an area of 199 rai (32 hectares) in the [[Si Racha District]] of [[Chonburi Province]].\n{{colbegin}}\n* Faculty of Management Sciences\n* Faculty of Engineering at Sriracha\n* Faculty of Science at Sriracha\n* Faculty of Economics at Sriracha\n* Faculty of International Maritime Studies\n{{colend}}\n\n===Chalermphrakiat Sakon Nakhon Province Campus===\nThe Chalermphakiat Sakon Nakhon Province Campus was established in 1996 to commemorate the Golden Jubilee Anniversary of His Majesty King Bhumibol Adulyadej\u2019s Accession to the Throne. The campus occupies the area of 4,488 rai (718 hectares) in [[Mueang Sakon Nakhon District|Mueang District]] of [[Sakon Nakhon Province]].\n* Faculty of Natural Resources and Agro-Industry\n* Faculty of Science and Engineering\n* Faculty of Liberal Arts and Management Sciences\n* Faculty of Public Health\n\n===Affiliated Institute===\n* Irrigation College\n* Boromrajonani College of Nursing Napparat Vajira\n\n==Academic profile==\n\n===Rankings===\nThe [[QS World University Rankings|QS World University Rankings 2020]] ranked Kasetsart University 127th in Asia and 801-1000th in the world. In addition, the QS World University Rankings by Subject 2020, the university was ranked 51-100th in Agriculture & Forestry, 251-300th in Environmental Studies, 351-400th in Engineering - Chemical, 401-450th in Chemistry, and 451-500th in Biological Sciences and Engineering - Mechanical and Aeronautical & Manufacturing.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.topuniversities.com/universities/kasetsart-university |title=Kasetsart University|website=Top Universities|access-date=2020-03-05}}</ref> Kasetsart was ranked 29th in Agriculture and Forestry worldwide in the QS World University Rankings 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.topuniversities.com/university-rankings/university-subject-rankings/2017/agriculture-forestry|title=Agriculture and Forestry University Rankings|access-date=}}</ref> It was ranked in the 651-700 [[tranche]] in the [[QS World University Rankings|QS World University Rankings 2015\u20132016]].<ref>{{cite web|title=QS World University Rankings 2015/16|url=http://www.topuniversities.com/university-rankings/world-university-rankings/2015#sorting=rank+region=+country=+faculty=+stars=false+search=|website=QS Top Universities|accessdate=21 November 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Times Higher Education|Times Higher Education World University Rankings 2017\u20132018]] ranked Kasetsart University in the 800-1000 tier in the world and 251-300th in the [[BRICS]] and Emerging Economies.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.timeshighereducation.com/world-university-rankings/kasetsart-university |title=Kasetsart University World University Rankings|website=Times Higher Education|access-date=2018-02-11}}</ref>\n\n===Research===\n[[File:Kasetsart University Thailand Logo Board.jpg|thumb|175px|right|Institute of Food Research and Product Development]]\n\n* '''Institute of Food Research and Product Development'''\nThe Institute of Food Research and Product Development (IFRPD), is a [[food science|science]] and [[food technology]] research institute, with the mandate to provide information and services to society as well as research in support of governmental policies to resolve the country's economic problems related to agricultural products.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ifrpd.ku.ac.th/en/about/index.php |title=Introduced organization|website=Institute of Food Research and Product Development|access-date=2017-01-03}}</ref>\n\n* '''Kasetsart Agricultural and Agro-Industrial Product Improvement Institute'''\nKasetsart Agricultural and Agro-Industrial Product Improvement Institute (KAPI), is an [[agricultural]] and [[food industry|agro-industrial product]] research institute, established on 29 July 1991 to research and develop [[quality standards]] in non-food innovation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.kapi.ku.ac.th/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=50&Itemid=57 |title=About us|website=Kasetsart Agricultural and Agro-Industrial Product Improvement Institute|access-date=2017-01-03}}</ref>\n\n* '''Kasetsart University Research and Development Institute'''\nKasetsart University Research and Development Institute (KURDI) administers and coordinates research projects and research efforts.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www3.rdi.ku.ac.th/?page_id=5549|title=Introduced organization|website=Kasetsart University Research and Development Institute|access-date=2017-03-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170312045608/http://www3.rdi.ku.ac.th/?page_id=5549|archive-date=12 March 2017|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n* '''Kasetsart University Institute for Advanced Studies'''\nKasetsart University Institute for Advanced Studies (KUIAS) consists of four research centers: the Center for Advanced Studies for Agriculture and Food; the Center for Advanced Studies in Tropical Natural Resources; the Center for Advanced Studies in Nanotechnology for Chemical, Food and Agricultural Industries; and the Center for Advanced Studies In Industrial Technology. They are responsible for carrying out targeted research initiatives.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://research.rdi.ku.ac.th/forest/Home.aspx |title=Kasetsart University Research |website=KU forest|access-date=2017-01-04}}</ref>\n\n* '''Center for Excellence in Silk'''\nHoused at Kasetsart University's Kamphaeng Saen Campus, the center is a provider of silkworm eggs and know-how to Thai farmers.<ref name=BP-20170219>{{cite news|last1=Wangkiat|first1=Paritta|title=Ericulture reeling them in|url=http://www.bangkokpost.com/news/special-reports/1201117/ericulture-reeling-them-in|accessdate=19 February 2017|work=Bangkok Post|date=19 February 2017|url-access=subscription }}</ref>\n\n== International programs ==\n=== Undergraduate programs ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" width=100%\n|-\n! colspan = \"5\" style = \"background: #00675A; color: White; \" | Undergraduate programs\n|-\n! style= \"background: #9FAA00; color:White; \" width=15% | Campus\n! style= \"background: #9FAA00; color:White; \" width=15% | Faculty\n! style= \"background: #9FAA00; color:White; \" width=10% | Degree\n! style= \"background: #9FAA00; color:White; \" width=50% | Program\n! style= \"background: #9FAA00; color:White; \" width=10% | Duration\n|-\n| valign = \"center\" rowspan=\"18\" | Bangkhen\n| valign = \"top\"