             = <!-- Remove or comment out this parameter line completely if URL exists on or is moved to Wikidata; use |website_title= to change the display title. -->\n| production_website       = <!-- use |production_website_title= to change the display title. -->\n}}\n'''''Never Have I Ever''''' is an American [[coming of age]] [[dramedy]] television series on [[Netflix]] starring [[Tamil Canadian]] actress [[Maitreyi Ramakrishnan]] and created by [[Mindy Kaling]] and Lang Fisher. It premiered on April 27, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2020/tv/news/tv-news-roundup-netflix-releases-trailer-mindy-kalings-never-have-i-ever-1234581321/|title=TV News Roundup: Netflix Releases 'Never Have I Ever' Trailer (Watch)|last=Shafer|first=Ellise|date=April 15, 2020|website=Variety|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=April 16, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/entertainment/ramakrishnan-mindy-kaling-netflix-1.5265663|title='Be that change': Maitreyi Ramakrishnan on starring in Mindy Kaling's new comedy|date=August 30, 2019|work=CBC|access-date=April 16, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vulture.com/2020/04/watch-mindy-kaling-never-have-i-ever-trailer-netflix.html|title=Dear Gods, Meet Devi, a Young Mindy Kaling in Netflix's Never Have I Ever|last=Murphy|first=Chris|date=April 15, 2020|website=Vulture|language=en-us|access-date=April 16, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nowtoronto.com/api/content/274c2a2a-7e6e-11ea-9bdd-1244d5f7c7c6/|title=Maitreyi Ramakrishnan talks TikTok drama, sex and embracing Tamil culture|last=Simonpillai|first=Radheyan|date=April 14, 2020|website=NOW Magazine|language=en-us|access-date=April 16, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.teenvogue.com/story/netflix-never-have-i-ever-messy-teenhood|title=\"Never Have I Ever\" Stars Promise Real, Messy Teenhood|last=Jaime|first=Angie|website=Teen Vogue|language=en|access-date=April 16, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://collider.com/never-have-i-ever-netflix-trailer-release-date-mindy-kaling/|title='Never Have I Ever' Trailer Reveals Mindy Kaling's New Netflix Show|last=Lawrence|first=Gregory|date=April 15, 2020|website=Collider|language=en-US|access-date=April 16, 2020}}</ref> The series has received positive reviews from critics.<ref name=\"RottenTomatoes\">{{Cite web|title=Never Have I Ever: Season 1|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/never_have_i_ever/s01|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|access-date=April 29, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Metacritic\">{{Cite web|title=Never Have I Ever|url=https://www.metacritic.com/tv/never-have-i-ever|website=[[Metacritic]]|access-date=April 29, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nAfter a horrible year, Devi Vishwakumar ([[Maitreyi Ramakrishnan]]) wants to change her social status, but friends, family, and feelings would not make it easy on her. \n==Cast==\n===Main===\n* [[Maitreyi Ramakrishnan]] as Devi Vishwakumar, a sophomore student who wants to improve her life.<ref name=\"Cast\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.teenvogue.com/story/never-have-i-ever-cast|title=Meet the Cast of Netflix's \"Never Have I Ever,\" Your Next Fave Teen Comedy|last=Maloney|first=Alli|website=Teen Vogue|language=en|access-date=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Darren Barnet]] as Paxton Hall-Yoshida, a classmate of Devi's who is retaking the year.<ref name=\"Cast\"/>\n* [[Ramona Young]] as Eleanor, one of Devi's best friends who enjoys acting.<ref name=\"Cast\"/>\n* Lee Rodriguez as Fabiola, Devi's other best friend who enjoys science.<ref name=\"Cast\"/>\n* Richa Moorjani as Kamala, Devi's cousin who is staying with her while she is completing her PhD.<ref name=\"Cast\"/>\n* Jaren Lewison as Ben Gross, Devi's nemesis at school.<ref name=\"Cast\"/>\n* [[John McEnroe]] as Himself, the narrator of the series.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Petski |first1=Denise |title=John McEnroe To Narrate Netflix\u2019s Kaling/Fisher Comedy Series \u2018Never Have I Ever\u2019 |url=https://deadline.com/2019/09/john-mcenroe-narrate-netflix-kaling-fisher-comedy-series-never-have-i-ever-1202731927/ |website=[[Deadline Hollywood|Deadline]] |accessdate=April 23, 2020 |date=September 11, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Poorna Jagannathan]] as Dr. Nalini Vishwakumar, Devi's mother.<ref name=\"Cast\" />\n\n===Recurring===\n* [[Niecy Nash]] as Dr. Jamie Ryan, Devi\u2019s therapist.<ref name=\"Cast\" />\n* [[Sendhil Ramamurthy]] as Mohan Venkatesan, Devi's dead father who appears in flashbacks.\n* Benjamin Norris as Trent Harrison, Paxton's friend.\n* Adam Shapiro as Mr. Shapiro, a history teacher.\n* Martin Martinez as Oliver Martinez, Eleanor's boyfriend.\n* Christina Kartchner as Eve, a girl who has a crush on Fabiola.\n* Jack Seavor McDonald as Eric Perkins, an unpopular student.\n* Dino Petrera as Jonah Sharpe, a boy who comes out as gay.\n* Eddie Liu as Steve, Kamala\u2019s secret boyfriend \n* Lily D. Moore as Rebecca, Paxton\u2019s adopted sister\n* Hanna Stein as Shira, Ben\u2019s girlfriend\n* [[Angela Kinsey]] as Vivian, Ben's mother.\n* [[Michael Badalucco]] as Howard, Ben's father.\n* Donna Pieroni as Patty, Ben's housekeeper.\n* [[Andy Samberg]] as Himself, the narrator for Ben Gross's thoughts\n* Rushi Kota as Prashant, Kamala's date for an arranged marriage\n\n==Episodes==\n=== Season 1 (2020) ===\n{{Episode table |total_width= |background=#DE14CD |overall= |title= |director= |writer= |airdate= |airdateR=<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.salon.com/2020/04/27/never-have-i-ever-review-netflix-mindy-kaling/|title=Mindy Kaling's smart teen sex romp \"Never Have I Ever\" may be her best series yet|work=[[Salon (website)|Salon]]|date=April 27, 2020}}</ref> |released=y |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 1\n |Title           = Pilot\n |DirectedBy      = [[Tristram Shapeero]]\n |WrittenBy       = [[Mindy Kaling]] & Lang Fisher\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|27}}\n |ShortSummary    = After her dad dies and she is in a wheelchair for her freshman year, Devi comes up with a plan to have a good sophomore year. She pleads with best friends Eleanor and Fabiola to get boyfriends, so that the group become cool. However, when she discovers that Eleanor has a boyfriend, she has a breakdown and asks classmate Paxton if he wants to have sex. Devi's cousin Kamala is told that her marriage is being arranged. \n |LineColor       = DE14CD\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 2\n |Title           = ... had sex with Paxton Hall-Yoshida\n |DirectedBy      = Tristram Shapeero\n |WrittenBy       = Justin Noble\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|27}}\n |ShortSummary    = Devi leaves orchestra practice early to go to Paxton's house, but leaves when she does not feel ready to have sex. Kamala meets with her secret boyfriend, and tells him that she cannot see him anymore due to her arranged marriage.\n |LineColor       = DE14CD\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 3\n |Title           = ... gotten drunk with the popular kids\n |DirectedBy      = [[Linda Mendoza]]\n |WrittenBy       = Amina Munir\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|27}}\n |ShortSummary    = In history class, Devi is delighted when Paxton asks her to be in his group, but overhears him saying he asked her to get a good grade. Eleanor and Fabiola team up with Eve, who Fabiola has a crush on. Fabiola then breaks up with her boyfriend and realises she is gay. Devi invites herself to a party, and sees Paxton flirting with a girl. A drunk Devi sees a coyote at the party, and believing it has the spirit of her dad, she talks to it. It attacks her, and she is taken to the hospital. Paxton sees her in hospital, and affirms that they are just friends. Inspired by a ''[[Riverdale (2017 TV series)|Riverdale]]'' scene, Kamala reconciles with her boyfriend.\n |LineColor       = DE14CD\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 4\n |Title           = ... felt super Indian\n |DirectedBy      = Linda Mendoza\n |WrittenBy       = Mindy Kaling\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|27}}\n |ShortSummary    = At a Hindu convention at the school, Devi's mother Nalini asks Devi to smooth talk Ron, who is on the college admission board. Ron asks Devi to use her dad's death and her paralysis as a story to get into college, but she refuses. At the convention, Kamala meets a woman who is shunned due to refusing her arranged marriage. She tells Kamala to go ahead with her marriage. \n |LineColor       = DE14CD\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 5\n |Title           = ... started a nuclear war\n |DirectedBy      = [[Kabir Akhtar]]\n |WrittenBy       = Chris Schleicher & Akshara Sekar\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|27}}\n |ShortSummary    = Fabiola gathers her family members to [[come out]], but avoids telling them. Paxton tells Eleanor that her mother served them in a restaurant, despite her being told that she is working on a cruise as an actress. Fabiola accompanies her to the restaurant, where they see her mother. Afterwards, she comes out to Eleanor, who supports her. Devi joins [[Model United Nations|Model UN]], and fuels the lie that she and Paxton are sleeping together. She and nemesis Ben join forces to get the members alcohol. The next day, Devi turns against him in UN, and gets the members to stand alongside her. Paxton then confronts her and asks why she would use him.\n |LineColor       = DE14CD\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 6\n |Title           = ... been the loneliest boy in the world\n |DirectedBy      = Kabir Akhtar\n |WrittenBy       = Aaron Geary & Ben Steiner\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|27}}\n |ShortSummary    = Ben returns home from Model UN to his mother leaving for a self realisation resort. Planning to see a game court-side with his girlfriend and father, both cancel on him, so he gives the tickets to his housekeeper. Feeling lonely, he meets with a friend from an online forum, who turns out to be a 50-year-old man. Ben sees Nalini about a pimple, and she invites him to a dinner with her and the Vishwakumars. Initially upset with Ben coming over, Devi is pleasantly surprised when he does not expose her behavior at Model UN.\n |LineColor       = DE14CD\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 7\n |Title           = ... been a big, fat liar\n |DirectedBy      = Anu Valia\n |WrittenBy       = Erica Oyama\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|27}}\n |ShortSummary    = Devi tries to make it up to Eleanor and Fabiola. She visits Eleanor's mother and tells her to talk to Eleanor. She comes to the school and watches Eleanor rehearse for the play, but leaves midway through to go back to broadway. Distraught, Eleanor quits acting. Fabiola asks Devi to support her, but when Paxton texts her, she goes to his house instead.\n |LineColor       = DE14CD\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 8\n |Title           = ... pissed off everyone I know\n |DirectedBy      = Anu Valia\n |WrittenBy       = Chris Schleicher\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|27}}\n |ShortSummary    = Eleanor and Fabiola decide to take a break from Devi, so she goes to see her therapist. She tells Devi that all the drama is coming from the grief over her dad, and Devi says that she wants a new therapist. Ben throws a party for his birthday, and after Devi finds Kamala with boyfriend Steve, she makes Kamala sneak her to the party. After Devi learns that a classmate ruined the punch, she sees Fabiola about to drink it. She goes to swipe the drink from her, but accidentally spills the bowl of punch over her. Fabiola argues with her in front of the crowd, and accidentally comes out. Eve, who overheard, arranges a date with her. After Devi falls in the pool, Paxton takes her home and kisses her.\n |LineColor       = DE14CD\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 9\n |Title           = ... had to be on my best behavior\n |DirectedBy      = Tristram Shapeero\n |WrittenBy       = [[Matt Warburton]]\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|27}}\n |ShortSummary    = Kamala's arranged husband meets with the family over lunch for the first time. Devi enters Kamala's room to place a present that she got only to find that Steve is in there, waiting to rescue Kamala from her arrainged marriage. At Devi's behest, Kamala talk with Steve to sort things out. Nalini walks in on them and reveals that she knew about the two as a couple. Paxton arrives to return Devi's dress from the party, and accidentally reveals that Devi secretly attended Ben's party and that she and Paxton kissed. Nalini, enraged, yells at Paxton for \"ruining\" Devi's life. Devi's uncle reveals that Nalini is planning on moving them both to India. Devi gets in a fight with Nalini, and refuses to move.\n |LineColor       = DE14CD\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 10\n |Title           = ... said I'm sorry\n |DirectedBy      = Tristram Shapeero\n |WrittenBy       = Lang Fisher\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|27}}\n |ShortSummary    = Paxton avoids Devi following with incident with Nalini. Devi moves in with Ben so that she cannot be moved to India. Nalini visits her on Mohan's birthday and asks her to spread her father's ashes with her, but she refuses. To convince Devi to spread the ashes with Nalini, Ben enlists the help of Fabiola and Eleanor, who reconcile their friendship. They encourage Devi to go, so Ben takes her to Malibu. Devi, Nalini and Kamala spread Mohan's ashes and she agrees to move back in with them. Returning to Ben's car, the pair kiss. Meanwhile, Paxton, at his sister's urging to reconcile with Devi, leaves her a message while waiting at her front door.\n |LineColor       = DE14CD\n}}\n}}\n\n== Reception ==\n<!--AUDIENCE RECEPTION AND RATINGS: Do not include them! Wikipedia does not support user-generated content in its articles, and thus audience ratings cannot be included. Please refer to the talk page before proceeding to edit this section, and view the multiple discussions raised on the topic. No consensus has been formed to allow this a