ominated work\n! Result\n! Ref\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|2017\n| [[53rd Baeksang Arts Awards|53rd]] [[Baeksang Arts Awards]]\n| Most Popular - Actor (Film)\n| rowspan=\"2\" |''[[A Stray Goat]]''\n| rowspan=\"2\" {{nom}}\n|<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.hancinema.net/53rd-baeksang-arts-awards-2017--most-popular-actor-in-a-movie-nominees-list-104887.html |title=53rd Baeksang Arts Awards 2017 : Most Popular Actor in a Movie Nominees List |date=10 April 2017 |access-date=10 October 2017 |publisher=[[HanCinema]]}}</ref> \n|-\n| 12th Max Movie Awards\n| Rising Star Award\n|<ref>{{Cite news |last=Joe Yoon |url=http://news.maxmovie.com/312942 |title=2017 \ub77c\uc774\uc9d5 \uc2a4\ud0c0 11 - \ubc15\uc9c4\uc601 \u201c\uc9c4\uc9c0\ud558\uc9c0 \uc54a\uc73c\uba74 \ubd80\ub044\ub7ec\uc6b8 \uac83 \uac19\uc558\ub2e4\u201d |date=17 April 2017 |work=Max Movie Magazine |access-date=10 October 2017 |issue=40 |trans-title=11 Rising Stars of 2017 - Interview with Park Jin-young \"I thought it would be ashamed if I didn't do it seriously\"}}</ref>\n|-\n|2019\n|StarHub Night of Stars\n|Favourite Korean Drama Male Character\n|''[[He Is Psychometric]]''\n|{{Won}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.zaobao.com.sg/zentertainment/movies-and-tv/story20191125-1008154 |title=\u300a\u661f\u548c\u7480\u74a8\u661f\u5149\u591c\u300b \u91d1\u6750\u6631\u6734\u654f\u82f1\u6700\u53d7\u77a9\u76ee |date=2019-11-25 |language=zh |access-date=2019-11-25}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Park Jin-young (born 1994)}}\n* {{IMDb name|4917074}}\n* [http://www.jyppub.com/creators2?schDisplay=&schType=&schString=&pageNo=1&creator_cd=CR00049&creator_pm=Jin%20Young Jinyoung] on JYP Publishing\n\n{{Got7}}\n{{JYP Entertainment}}{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Park, Jin-young}}\n[[Category:1994 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Got7 members]]\n[[Category:JYP Entertainment artists]]\n[[Category:South Korean male film actors]]\n[[Category:South Korean male idols]]\n[[Category:South Korean male singers]]\n[[Category:South Korean male television actors]]\n[[Category:South Korean pop singers]]\n[[Category:King of Mask Singer contestants]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|South Korean singer and actor}}\n{{For|the founder of [[JYP Entertainment]]|J. Y. Park}}\n{{Korean name|Park}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Park Jin-young\n| image              = Park Jinyoung (1994) at 2018 KBS Song Festival, 28 December 2018 01.jpg\n| image_size         = \n| caption            = Park Jinyoung at 2018 KBS Song Festival, 28 December 2018\n| birth_name         = Park Jin-young\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1994|9|22}}\n| birth_place        = [[Jinhae-gu]], [[Changwon]], [[South Korea]]\n| residence          = [[Seoul]], South Korea\n| education          = [[Howon University]]\n| occupation         = {{hlist|Singer-songwriter|dancer|actor}}\n| module             = {{Infobox musical artist|embed=yes\n| background      = solo_singer\n| genre           = [[K-pop]]\n| instrument      = Vocals\n| years_active    = 2012\u2013present\n| label           = [[JYP Entertainment|JYP]]\n| associated_acts = {{hlist|[[JJ Project (South Korean Duo)|JJ Project]]|[[Got7]]|JYP Nation|JYP Actors}}\n| module          = {{Infobox Korean name|child=yes\n| title           = [[Korean name]]\n| hangul          = {{linktext|\ubc15|\uc9c4|\uc601}}\n| hanja           = {{linktext|\u6734|\u73cd|\u69ae}}\n| rr              = Bak Jin-yeong\n| mr              = Pak Chiny\u014fng\n}}}}\n}}\n\n'''Park Jin-young''' (born September 22, 1994), referred to as '''Jinyoung''', is a South Korean singer-songwriter, dancer and actor.<ref name=\"naver dispatch\">{{Cite web |url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=420&aid=0000000709 |title=[STARCAST] Should we try a self intro? \u2018Me\u2019 Written by the Pens of 'GOT7\u2019 |last=Dispatch |date=28 January 2014 |website=Naver |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://archive.is/20161015211348/http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=420&aid=0000000709 |archive-date=15 October 2016 |access-date=13 October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://thestar.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2014/02/25/2014022502729.html |title=Self-introduction of Mark, Jackson, JB and Jinyoung |date=27 February 2014 |website=The Star |publisher=Chosun |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161015200527/http://thestar.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2014/02/25/2014022502729.html |archive-date=15 October 2016 |access-date=13 October 2016}}</ref> He is a member of the boy band [[Got7]] and boy band duo [[JJ Project]].<ref name=\"Notice of Got7 Jr. Name Change\">{{Cite web |url=http://got7.jype.com/notice.asp?idx=61&page=&vnum=6 |title=Notice of Got7 Jr. Name Change |website=got7.jype.com |access-date=29 May 2015}}</ref> He made his acting debut in the drama ''[[Dream High 2]]'' (2012) followed by supporting roles in ''[[When a Man Falls in Love]]'' (2013), ''[[This is My Love]]'' (2015), ''[[Legend of the Blue Sea]]'' (2016-2017) and as main role in ''[[He Is Psychometric]]'' (2019). He made his film debut in the independent film ''[[A Stray Goat]]'' (2016).\n\nDue to his shared name with his [[JYP Entertainment|agency]]'s [[J. Y. Park|founder]], Park originally debuted with the stage name '''Jr.''',<ref name=\"naver dispatch\" /> but he later changed the spelling to '''Junior''' due to widespread confusion about the correct pronunciation of his name.<ref name=\"Notice of Got7 Jr. Name Change\" /> On August 16, 2016, Park announced that he would simply go by his given name.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://twitter.com/jrjyp/status/765512335783972865 |title=\ubc15\uc9c4\uc601 on Twitter |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161015204513/https://twitter.com/jrjyp/status/765512335783972865?lang=de |archive-date=15 October 2016 |access-date=26 August 2016}}</ref>\n\n== Biography ==\nJinyoung wanted to be an entertainer since childhood and appear on TV.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web |url=https://news.kstyle.com/article.ksn?articleNo=1986868 |title=GOT7\u3001\u82b8\u80fd\u4eba\u3078\u306e\u61a7\u308c\u304b\u3089\u6bcd\u89aa\u306e\u5f71\u97ff\u307e\u3067\u2026\u50d5\u305f\u3061\u304c\u6b4c\u624b\u306b\u306a\u3063\u305f\u7406\u7531 - INTERVIEW - \u97d3\u6d41\u30fb\u97d3\u56fd\u82b8\u80fd\u30cb\u30e5\u30fc\u30b9\u306fKstyle |website=Kstyle |language=ja |url-status=live |access-date=2020-02-05}}</ref> He started learning to dance, but he didn't take it seriously for the first three months, until his father reproached him.<ref name=\":0\" /> After three months of intense practicing, he was able to dance,<ref name=\":0\" /> and in 2009 he successfully auditioned for [[JYP Entertainment]], winning first place at the open audition with [[JB (South Korean singer)|JB]].<ref name=\"Donga-JJproject\">{{Cite web |url=http://news.donga.com/3/all/20120524/46500868/5 |title=JJ\ud504\ub85c\uc81d\ud2b8, \ubc15\uc9c4\uc601\u00b7\uc784\uc7ac\ubc94 \uc774\ub984\uc5d0 \uae08\ud14c\uae4c\uc9c0 \ub458\ub800\ub2e4 ''[JJ Project, to combine the names of Jinyoung and Jaebeom]'' |publisher=Donga.com |language=ko |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161026195250/http://news.donga.com/3/all/20120524/46500868/5 |archive-date=26 October 2016 |access-date=20 July 2015}}</ref> At that time he only liked dancing, but, thinking seriously about his future, he realized that he loved music as a whole.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nHe attended Gyeonggi High School and Howon University.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://m.metroseoul.co.kr/news/newsview?newscd=2014011900071 |title=\uac13\uc138\ube10 '\uc6b0\ub9ac\ub9cc\uc758 \uae38 \uc788\uc5b4 \uc5d1\uc18c \ubd80\ub7fd\uc9c0 \uc54a\uc544'(\uc778\ud130\ubdf0) |website=Metro Seoul |language=ko |url-status=live |access-date=2020-02-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.dispatch.co.kr/28172 |title=[\uc2a4\ud0c0\uce90\uc2a4\ud2b8] \"\uc790\uae30\ub97c \uc18c\uac1c\ud560\uae4c\uc694?\"\u2026'\uac13\uc138\ube10', \uc790\ud544\ub85c \uc4f4 '\ub098' |date=2014-01-28 |website=Dispatch |language=ko-KR |url-status=live |access-date=2020-02-05}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2020, it was reported that Park had donated an undisclosed amount of money to wild animals affected by fires in Australia.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=609&aid=0000243355 |title=JYP \uce21 \u201c\uac13\uc138\ube10 \uc9c4\uc601, \ud638\uc8fc\uc0b0\ubd88 \ud53c\ud574 \uc57c\uc0dd\ub3d9\ubb3c \uc704\ud574 \uae30\ubd80\u201d |website=entertain.naver.com |language=ko |access-date=2020-02-15}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n\n===2011\u20132013: Debut and career beginnings===\nIn 2011, Jinyoung was cast in the role of Jung Ui-bong in the television drama ''[[Dream High 2]]''.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/2778/full-cast-of-dream-high-2-unveiled |title=A Peek at Dream High 2's Couples |last=Oh |first=Mi-jung |date=15 January 2012 |website=Mwave |access-date=19 January 2012}}</ref> The drama began airing on January 30, 2012 on [[Korean Broadcasting System|KBS]].<ref>{{cite web|last=|first=|title=\n'Dream High Season 2' To Begin|url=http://www.hancinema.net/-dream-high-season-2-to-begin-37698.html|website=Hancinema|date=January 19, 2012|accessdate=August 6, 2017}}</ref> On February 29, Park released the song \"We Are The B\" for the drama's soundtrack, along with [[Jinwoon]], [[Kang So-ra]] and [[Kim Ji-soo (singer, born 1990)|Kim Ji-soo]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://sports.donga.com/3/02/20120228/44381261/2 |title=\u2018\ub4dc\ub9bc\ud558\uc7742\u2019 B\uae09\uc778\uc0dd, \uacbd\ucf8c\ud55c \uba5c\ub85c\ub514 \u2018\uc778\uae30 \ud3ed\ubc1c\u2019 |date=28 February 2012 |website=Sports Donga}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2012, Jinyoung and fellow trainee [[JB (South Korean singer)|JB]] debuted as the duo [[JJ Project]] with the single album ''JJ Project Slot Machine''.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://news.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2012/05/21/2012052101179.html |title=JJ\ud504\ub85c\uc81d\ud2b8 '\ubc14\uc6b4\uc2a4', \uc544\uc774\ud2a0\uc988 10\uc704 '\uc131\uacf5\uc801 \ub370\ubdd4 \uc2e0\uace0\uc2dd' |date=21 May 2012 |publisher=[[The Chosun Ilbo]] |access-date=December 31, 2014}}</ref> Their official music video for title track \"''Bounce''\" was released on May 19, and the duo began promotions for \"Bounce\" on ''[[M! Countdown]]'' on May 24.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/7016/jj-project-takes-over-youtube-charts |title=JJ Project Takes Over Youtube Charts |date=22 May 2012 |publisher=MWave |access-date=31 December 2014}}</ref>\n\nOn March 11, 2013, it was announced that Jinyoung would be appearing as Ddol-yi on [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]]'s new drama ''[[When a Man Falls in Love]]''.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=311&aid=0000199564 |title=\uc8fc\ub2c8\uc5b4, '\ub0a8\uc790\uac00 \uc0ac\ub791\ud560 \ub54c' \uce90\uc2a4\ud305\u2026\uc1a1\uc2b9\ud5cc \u6bcd \uc54c\ubc14\uc0dd \uc5ed |date=15 March 2013 |website=Xports News |language=ko}}</ref> His bandmate [[JB (South Korean singer)|JB]] also had a role in the drama, which aired for twenty episodes beginning April 3.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://mwave.interest.me/en/kpop-news/article-print/31066/ |title=JJ Project\u2032s JB to Appear as Shin Se Kyung's Little Brother in 'When a Man Falls in Love' |last=Ko |first=Hung Ju |date=11 March 2013 |website=Mwave |access-date=6 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n===2014\u20132017: Debut with Got7, hosting, and film debut===\nOn January 16, 2014 [[JYP Entertainment]] debuted a new boy group called [[Got7]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://osen.mt.co.kr/article/G1109754242 |title=JYP, \ud3ec\uc2a4\ud2b8 2PM \uadf8\ub8f9\uba85\uc740 '\uac13\uc138\ube10(GOT7)'..16\uc77c \ub370\ubdd4\ubb34\ub300 |date=1 January 2014 |website=Osen |access-date=30 December 2014}}</ref>, their first since 2008 with [[2PM]]. Park was announced as a member of the seven piece group as a vocalist. Their first [[extended play|EP]]  was released soon after on January 20 titled ''[[Got It?]]'', which peaked at number two on the [[Gaon Album Chart]] and number one on Billboard's World Albums Chart. Park also made the choreography for one of the singles, ''Follow Me''.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/81233/interview-got7-talks-identify-building-teamwork-and-more |title=GOT7 Talks \u2032Identify,\u2032 Building Teamwork and More |last=Jee-Won |first=Jeong |website=Mwave |access-date=23 November 2014}}</ref> Aside from his activities with Got7, Park has participated in various music and acting projects. In 2015, he was cast in a supporting role in the drama ''[[This is My Love]]'', which aired on [[JTBC]] from May 29 to July 18.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201506181456351985361_2 |title=GOT7 member to feature in local magazine |last=Yoon Sarah |date=18 June 2015 |website=[[K-Pop Herald]] |access-date=2016-04-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.bntnews.co.uk/app/news.php?nid=20584 |title=Stills of Jr. From His First Filming Are Released |last=Ghim |first=Sora |date=1 May 2015 |website=BNT News |access-date=2016-04-23}}</ref> The same year in March he was hired as official host for [[M Countdown]] alongside [[Shinee]]'s [[Key (entertainer)|Key]], group member [[BamBam (singer)|BamBam]] and [[CNBLUE]]'s [[Lee Jung-shin|Jung-shin]].<ref name=\"mdown\">{{Cite web |url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=311&aid=0000450202 |title=\ud0a4 \uc774\uc815\uc2e0 '\uc5e0\uce74' \uc0c8 MC \uc804\uaca9\ubc1c\ud0c1\u2026\ud2b9\ubcc4\ubb34\ub300 \uccab\uc120 |website=Mnet |language=ko |trans-title=M Countdown hired new MC's |access-date=19 March 2015}}</ref> Jinyoung left his position as MC in March 2016 to focus on activities with Got7, including the group's first [[Fly Tour (Got7)|worldwide concert tour]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.newsen.com/news_view.php?uid=201603031933003510 |title=\uac13\uc138\ube10 \uc8fc\ub2c8\uc5b4-\ubc40\ubc40, \u2018\uc5e0\uce74\uc6b4\ud2b8\ub2e4\uc6b4\u2019 MC \ub5a0\ub09c\ub2e4..\ub9c8\uc9c0\ub9c9 \uc778\uc0ac |website=Newsen |language=ko |trans-title=Got7's Junior and Bambam leave, 'M Countdown' MC's final farewell |access-date=15 June 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, Jinyoung was cast as the male lead in the independent film ''[[A Stray Goat]]'', directed by Cho Jae-min. The film follows a high school student, played by Jinyoung, who moves to the town of Goseong where he meets a girl, who is an outcast because of rumors and suspicions about her father.<ref name=\"koreatimes\">{{Cite web |url=http://koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/culture/2016/04/135_202518.html |title=Over 200 movies featured at Jeonju Film Festival |last=Jason Bechervaise |date=13 April 2016 |website=Koreatimes |access-date=15 June 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://tenasia.hankyung.com/archives/824200 |title=GOT7 \uc8fc\ub2c8\uc5b4-\uc9c0\uc6b0 \u2018\ub208\ubc1c\u2019 \ucd2c\uc601\ud604\uc7a5 \uacf5\uac1c\u2026\uc124\ub808\ub294 \uccab\ub9cc\ub0a8\ud150\uc544\uc2dc\uc544 |last=Jung Shi-woo |date=6 January 2016 |website=TenAsia |language=ko |access-date=23 April 2016}}</ref> The movie was theatrically released on March 1, 2017 and premiered at the [[Jeonju International Film Festival#17th Jeonju International Film Festival (2016)|17th Jeonju International Film Festival]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Lim Jeong-yeo |url=http://www.kpopherald.com/view.php?ud=201702271052211438705_2 |title=[V Report Plus] Park Jin-young is very fond of \u2018A Stray Goat\u2019 |access-date=27 February 2017 |website=Kpop Herald}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Jo Hee Seon |url=http://www.bntnews.co.uk/app/news.php?nid=32983 |title=GOT7 Gathers At VIP Premiere of Movie A Stray Goat |access-date=24 February 2017 |website=Kpop Herald}}</ref><ref name=\"koreatimes\" /> \n\nIn September 2016, Jinyoung was cast for a supporting role in the drama ''[[Legend of the Blue Sea]]'', where he portrayed the teenage version of [[Lee Min-ho (actor, born 1987)|Lee Min-ho]]'s character, the protagonist of the series.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://m.star.naver.com/got7/news/end?id=8290245&langCode=ko |title=[\ub2e8\ub3c5] \uac13\uc138\ube10 \uc9c4\uc601, '\ud478\ub978 \ubc14\ub2e4\uc758 \uc804\uc124' \ud569\ub958 |access-date=27 February 2017 |language=ko |trans-title=GOT7's Jinyoung, joining 'Legend of Blue Sea' |website=Naver}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201611031717093382911_2 |title=New stills show \u2018The Legend of the Blue Sea\u2019 younger years cast |date=3 November 2016 |website=Kpop Herald}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2017, SBS announced Jinyoung, [[NCT (band)|NCT]]'s Doyoung, and [[Blackpink]]'s [[Jisoo (singer, born 1995)|Jisoo]] as the new fixed MCs of [[Inkigayo]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=213&aid=0000943154 |title='\uc778\uac00' PD \"\uac13\uc138\ube10 \uc9c4\uc601\u00b7\ube14\ub799\ud551\ud06c \uc9c0\uc218\u00b7NCT \ub3c4\uc601, \uc0c8 MC \ud655\uc815\"[\uacf5\uc2dd] |access-date=23 May 2017 |language=ko |trans-title='Inkigayo' PD \"Got7, Black Pink, NCT - New MC confirmed\" [Official]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.kpopherald.com/view.php?ud=201702021439179208169_2 |title=Jinyoung, Jisoo, Doyoung to host \u2018Inkigayo\u2019 |date=2 February 2017 |website=Kpop Herald}}</ref>\n\n===2018\u2013present: Transition to leading roles===\n[[File:\"He Is Psychometric\" cast at the press conference, 5 March 2019.jpg|thumb| right|250px|''He Is Psychometric'' cast at the press conference on March 5, 2019]]\nIn December 2018, Park landed his first lead role in the fantasy rom-com drama ''[[He Is Psychometric]]'' alongside [[Kim Kwon]], [[Kim Da-som]] and [[Shin Ye-eun]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201812061407159142496_2 |title=GOT7\u2019s Jinyoung turns into \u2018That Psychometric Guy\u2019 |last=Kim |first=Jee-min |date=6 December 2018 |website=Kpop Herald |access-date=6 December 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn 2020, Park is set to star in the television series ''[[When My Love Blooms]]'' alongside [[Yoo Ji-tae]], [[Lee Bo-young]] and Jeon So-nee.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://n.news.naver.com/entertain/now/article/382/0000788327 |title=\u2018\ud654\uc591\uc5f0\ud654\u2019 \uc720\uc9c0\ud0dc\u00d7\uc774\ubcf4\uc601\u00d7\ubc15\uc9c4\uc601\u00d7\uc804\uc18c\ub2c8 \uce90\uc2a4\ud305 \ub77c\uc778\uc5c5 \ud655\uc815 |last=Kwak |first=Hyun-soo |date=January 3, 2020 |website=Sports Donga |publisher=Naver |language=ko |access-date=January 3, 2020}}</ref> Park was also cast in the movie ''The Angel Without, The Devil Within'' where he's going to take the role as the Black Team's youngest member, a team of spies in foreign countries dedicated to overseas missions.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://n.news.naver.com/entertain/article/117/0003317918?l |title='\uc57c\ucc28', \uc624\ub298(31\uc77c) \ud06c\ub7ad\ud06c\uc778\u2026\"\uc124\uacbd\uad6cX\ubc15\ud574\uc218\u2192\uac13\uc138\ube10 \uc9c4\uc601 \ub4f1 \ud569\ub958\" [\uacf5\uc2dd] |last=Kim |first=Na-ra |date=December 31, 2019 |website=Naver |publisher=My Daily |language=ko |access-date=January 17, 2020}}</ref> The Korean title for the film, ''Yacha'', is based on the [[yaksha]] of Hindu mythology.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://news1.kr/articles/?3805387 |title=\uc124\uacbd\uad6c\u00b7\ubc15\ud574\uc218 \ub4f1, '\uc57c\ucc60' \ube14\ub799\ud300 6\uc778 \uce90\uc2a4\ud305 \ud655\uc815\u2026\ud06c\ub7ad\ud06c\uc778 |last=Jung |first=Yu-jin |date=December 31, 2019 |publisher=News1 |language=ko |access-date=January 17, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n{{Main|Got7 discography}}\n{{See also|JJ Project#Discography}}\n\n===Soundtrack appearances===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Year\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:12em;\" |Title\n! Peak chart<br>positions\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Sales<br><small>([[Music download|DL]])</small>\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Album\n|-\n! style=\"font-size:90%;\"